  Welcome to Week 1

Welcome to Week 1! We are STOKED to have you in this course.

In this week, we'll get started with the basics of AI filmmaking. We'll take a look at the current state of AI for filmmaking and talk about the limitations and possibilities of AI-assisted filmmaking. The first few lessons will be more conceptual, but we'll get into the nitty-gritty details about how to utilize the technical side of the tools as well.

We'll hit the ground running by showing you the tools needed to create AI content. You'll also get your hands dirty by creating your own film concepts and scripts using AI. We'll also create a realistic storyboard using Midjourney.

By the end of this week, you’ll be able to create a basic pitch and storyboard for a film.

Note: All artwork in this course is AI generated unless otherwise stated.

Week 1 Goals:

  • Understand the Context of AI Tools in a Filmmaking Pipeline
  • Learn the Ethical Considerations of Using AI
  • Learn a Simple Pipeline for Creating AI Projects
  • Learn Essential Storytelling Concepts
  • Find Resources for Ongoing Learning
  • Get Started with AI Concepting and Screenwriting
  • Learn to Create Basic AI Artwork
  • Create a Basic Storyboard
  • Create a Basic Pitch

Below is a syllabus for the course. Feel free to reference the syllabus to gain insight into the core concepts you will learn throughout the course.

Quick Course Breakdown:

  • Week 1: AI Basics and Screenwriting
  • Week 2: Directing AI
  • Week 3: AI Cinematography
  • Week 4: AI VFX and Animation
